description: Lander Medical Clinic & Western Family Care are a large multi-specialty group medical practice. We are physician owned and locally operated with an emphasis on primary care. Our clinicians include physicians, physician assistants, and nurse practitioners who practice in Behavioral Health, Family Medicine, Internal Medicine, Gynecology, Pediatrics and Same-Day Care in a caring and trusted environment. We also provide on-site services of lab, x-ray, mammography, ultrasound, echo cardiograms and stress tests, along with infusion.

name: Cory J. Lamblin, MD
description: Dr. Lamblin treats a wide variety of orthopaedic injuries and conditions such as knee and hip arthritis, and the treatment of complex fractures. Dr, Lamblin has particular clinical interests in orthopaedic trauma and sports-related injuries. Dr. Lamblin has specialized expertise in arthroscopic (less invasive) procedures to treat a wide variety of shoulder and knee injuries. An increasing array of injuries are able to be treated with arthroscopic surgery techniques. Shoulder injuries frequently treated by arthroscopy include rotator cuff, biceps tendon, and labral injuries. Knee Injuries commonly treated with arthroscopy include ligament injuries (such as ACL and MCL tears), meniscus tears, and cartilage damage.
